patiently waiting for `boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in documentation_summary: The HTML text is about the `mypy-boto3-dataexchange` package version 1.34.0, available on PyPI for download. This package provides type annotations for the `boto3.DataExchange` service, facilitating compatibility with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright. It's generated using `mypy-boto3-builder` version 7.21.0 and requires Python version 3.7 or higher. The package, licensed under the MIT License, is authored by Vlad Emelianov and supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.7 to 3.13. It aims to enhance code quality by enabling type checking and code completion without requiring explicit type annotations in user code.
